 } } \right]$$<br><br>Given $${({x^2} + 1)^2} + {x^2} = 109$$<br><br>Let $${x^2} + 1$$ = t<br><br>$${t^2} + t - 1 = 109$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ (t $$ - $$ 10) (t + 11) = 0<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ t = 10 = x<sup>2</sup> + 1 = a<sub>22</sub>
